14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-401 of Title 26, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. The Secretary of the State Election Board or the secretary
19 of a county election board shall not implement any new official
20 directive or guidance issued by a federal agency without prior
21 approval of the State Legislature. Provided, if the Legislature is
22 not in session when such a directive or guidance is received, it may
23 be implemented upon the written approval of the Speaker of the
